cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the collaboration among servers, communication network, and power network to reduce power consumption in cloud computing environments. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes policies and algorithms for collaboration among servers to reduce power consumption. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes signaling sequences to exchange information on power consumption between network and servers. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a method of estimating the volume of power consumption by all network devices and assigning it to an individual user, which could have security implications. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes algorithms for collaboration among servers to reduce power consumption.
